---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Roadmap | Superior">
  <section class="page-hero compact">
    <p class="eyebrow">Roadmap</p>
    <h1>Ship the safe and trustworthy parts first.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Superior is not trying to skip straight to "free money." The roadmap starts with education, paper execution, and reliable distribution before a broader live trading surface.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="workflow-band roadmap-band">
    <div class="workflow-steps">
      <article>
        <span>Now</span>
        <h3>Guided desktop product</h3>
        <p>Polymarket-first onboarding, explainable scanner results, paper bots, trust docs, and a clean Windows installer.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>Next</span>
        <h3>Broader venue depth</h3>
        <p>Kalshi data adapters, stronger exact-match tooling, and better cross-venue opportunity explanations.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>Later</span>
        <h3>Live execution maturation</h3>
        <p>Only after the unlock, risk, and paper layers are proven. Live trading will stay deterministic and heavily gated.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>Not now</span>
        <h3>No hosted bot runtime</h3>
        <p>Railway is for the public site only. User data, model keys, and trading controls remain local-first.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
